<TEXT>
   A small airplane that tried to hoist a banner
aloft from an airport and fly it over a professional football game
crashed Sunday, killing the pilot, a police official said.
   The Cessna 182 took off from Lunken Airport and had swooped back
over the airport low enough to hook a banner suspended between two
poles when the accident occurred around 1:30 p.m., said police
traffic officer Dan Katt.
   The plane lost power when it hooked the banner, Katt said. The
