<HEAD>Colombian Intelligence Officer, Peruvian Congressman Arrested</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MIAMI (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A Colombian intelligence officer who swallowed
drugs and a Peruvian congressman who failed to declare $25,000 in
cash have been arrested by U.S. Customs agents in separate
incidents, a spokesman said.
   Hernando Parra-Londono, a Colombian military intelligence
officer, was detained at Miami International Airport after getting
